headline: 1 in 5 Tractor Supply customers now raise chickens, thanks to egg inflation
summary: Tractor Supply has been leaning into its "Chick Days" as the high price of eggs has prompted a rising number of Americans to buy backyard chickens.

headline: 2 Reasons to Watch TSCO and 1 to Stay Cautious
summary: Over the last six months, Tractor Supply shares have sunk to $51.41, producing a disappointing 7% loss - worse than the S&P 500’s 1.6% drop. This was partly driven by its softer quarterly results and may have investors wondering how to approach the situation.
